records.addlTxt: 1:26 PM Defendant Dylan T. Shramek in court.  Attorney Carly June Sebion in court for Dylan T. Shramek.  Attorney Crystal Leigh Jensen in court for State of Wisconsin. State calls Deputy M. B., sworn, testifies to employment as a Sheriff's deputy in Jackson County. Record reflects identification of defendant. Testifies to conversation with victim 1, argument, escalated to violence. Cross-examination. No redirect. State calls Deputy J.D.; sworn, testifies working in his capacity of a Jackson County Deputy on 7/10/22. Spoke with victim. Cross examination. State makes argument, moves for bind over. Defense makes argument, asks Count 1 not be bound over. Court finds probable cause for bond over. Arraignment 11/21 @ 3 pm.
Preliminary hearing on November 1, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
